<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Parasitic</emphasis>
on living branches of bamboo. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Sexual morph</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ascostromata</emphasis>
1-6 cm long 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-4 cm wide, solitary, superficial, subglobose, long ellipsoid to irregular, tuberculate, fleshy, white to pinkish, with locules lining the periphery, with dark ostiolate points appearing on surface. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ascostromatic tissue</emphasis>
thick, pinkish, composed of wide, woven hyphae of textura intricata. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Locules</emphasis>
in vertical section 370-700 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
high 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
370-700 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
diam. (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">x̄</emphasis>
= 541 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
513 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, n = 20), globose to subglobose, immersed in the peripheral layer of ascostromata, with 100-200 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide ostioles. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Peridium</emphasis>
20-45 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
thick, composed of several layers of hyaline to light brown, small cells of textura angularis to textura intricata. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Hamathecium</emphasis>
composed of interthecial, hyaline septate, branched pseudoparaphyses, 1-2.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Asci</emphasis>
200-370 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
20-35 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">x̄</emphasis>
= 291.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
26.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, n = 20), 4-6-spored, thick-walled, bitunicate, fissitunicate, cylindrical, short-pedicellate, with an ocular chamber. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ascospores</emphasis>
50-77 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
15-24 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">x̄</emphasis>
= 62.3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
18.1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, n = 20), 1-seriate, overlapped, fusiform, muriform, hyaline, with 7 transverse septa, constricted at the septum, smooth-walled. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Asexual morph</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Conidiomata</emphasis>
200-500 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
high, 300-400 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide, loculate, forming within ascostromata, globose to subglobose or irregular. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Wall of locules</emphasis>
20-40 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
thick, composed of several layers of hyaline to light brown, small cells of textura intricata. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Conidiophores</emphasis>
reduced to conidiogenous cells. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Conidiogenous cells</emphasis>
3-6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">x̄</emphasis>
= 4.7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, n = 10), blastic, cylindrical, hyaline, smooth-walled. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Conidia</emphasis>
60-80 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
19-25 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">x̄</emphasis>
= 75.4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
23.1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, n = 20), fusiform, muriform, hyaline, with irregularly transverse and longitudinal septa, straight to curved, smooth-walled.
</paragraph>
