<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" family="Shiraiaceae" genus="Shiraia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Shiraia bambusicola" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bambusicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Shiraia bambusicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was erected by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hennings, P" journalOrPublisher="Botanische Jahrbuecher fuer Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="259 - 280" refId="B16" refString="Hennings, P, 1900. Fungi Japonici. . Botanische Jahrbuecher fuer Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie 28: 259 - 280" title="Fungi Japonici." volume="28" year="1900">Hennings (1900)</bibRefCitation>
, based on a collection from Japan. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.103.1.4" author="Liu, YX" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="51 - 60" refId="B34" refString="Liu, YX, Hyde, KD, Ariyawansa, HA, Li, WJ, Zhou, DQ, Yang, YL, Chen, YM, Liu, ZY, 2013. Shiraiaceae, new family of Pleosporales (Dothideomycetes, Ascomycota). . Phytotaxa 103: 51 - 60" title="Shiraiaceae, new family of Pleosporales (Dothideomycetes, Ascomycota)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.103.1.4" volume="103" year="2013">Liu et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
re-examined the holotype with 1-2.5 cm wide ascostromata, which is smaller than the new collections (1-4 cm wide in ascostromata) in China. The holotype has large ascospores compared with the new specimens in this study (75-125 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
23-47 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
vs. 50-77 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
15-24 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
). The epitype designated by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.103.1.4" author="Liu, YX" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="51 - 60" refId="B34" refString="Liu, YX, Hyde, KD, Ariyawansa, HA, Li, WJ, Zhou, DQ, Yang, YL, Chen, YM, Liu, ZY, 2013. Shiraiaceae, new family of Pleosporales (Dothideomycetes, Ascomycota). . Phytotaxa 103: 51 - 60" title="Shiraiaceae, new family of Pleosporales (Dothideomycetes, Ascomycota)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.103.1.4" volume="103" year="2013">Liu et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
which has similar-sized (50-77 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
15-24 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
) ascospores and similar ITS sequence, as in our new collections.
</paragraph>
